WEBVTT

00:19.479 --> 00:21.481
[♪♪♪]

00:58.810 --> 01:00.894
[♪♪♪]

01:00.895 --> 01:05.357
NARRATOR: <i>Once upon a time,
there was a king named William</i>

01:05.358 --> 01:08.944
<i>who ruled a large and mighty kingdom.</i>

01:08.945 --> 01:11.571
<i>And yet he was sad,</i>

01:11.572 --> 01:15.952
<i>for he was growing old and had
no child to inherit the throne.</i>

01:17.829 --> 01:22.332
<i>Then, happily, a daughter was born.</i>

01:22.333 --> 01:24.292
<i>A princess.</i>

01:24.293 --> 01:27.797
<i>And she was given the name Odette.</i>

01:30.258 --> 01:32.260
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:34.721 --> 01:39.641
<i>Kings and queens came from all around
to offer their gifts to the child.</i>

01:39.642 --> 01:45.773
<i>Among them was the widow Uberta
and her young son, Prince Derek.</i>

01:48.192 --> 01:53.864
<i>It was then that William and
Uberta happened upon the same idea.</i>

01:53.865 --> 02:00.036
<i>Derek and Odette would be brought together each
summer in hopes that they would fall in love</i>

02:00.037 --> 02:02.498
<i>and join their kingdoms forever.</i>

02:03.541 --> 02:06.626
<i>But unknown to all was another plan,</i>

02:06.627 --> 02:10.714
<i>that of the evil enchanter Rothbart.</i>

02:10.715 --> 02:15.093
<i>Odette's birth was of
little concern to him.</i>

02:15.094 --> 02:18.597
<i>For he was preparing to
take William's kingdom</i>

02:18.598 --> 02:21.391
<i>by means of the forbidden arts.</i>

02:21.392 --> 02:23.394
[♪♪♪]

02:27.190 --> 02:31.067
<i>On the eve of his
assault, William attacked,</i>

02:31.068 --> 02:34.322
<i>and Rothbart's powers were
plunged into darkness.</i>

02:38.534 --> 02:41.453
<i>Despite calls for his death,</i>

02:41.454 --> 02:43.497
<i>the enchanter was only banished.</i>

02:43.498 --> 02:44.414
[GRUNTS]

02:44.415 --> 02:46.917
I'm not finished with you yet, William.

02:46.918 --> 02:50.629
Someday I'll get my power back.

02:50.630 --> 02:56.009
And when I do, everything you
own, everything you love

02:56.010 --> 02:58.012
will be mine.

03:00.389 --> 03:03.476
<i>Many feared King William too kind.</i>

03:04.519 --> 03:08.021
<i>But in time, the threat was forgotten.</i>

03:08.022 --> 03:12.025
<i>And all hopes turned to
that not-too-distant summer,</i>

03:12.026 --> 03:15.655
<i>when Derek and Odette would meet.</i>

03:16.989 --> 03:18.657
[CHUCKLES]

03:18.658 --> 03:20.158
Here they come. Oh!

03:20.159 --> 03:22.161
[LAUGHING]

03:24.664 --> 03:26.581
[♪♪♪]

03:26.582 --> 03:27.625
[HORSE WHINNIES]

03:36.843 --> 03:38.302
[SHRIEKING]

03:40.346 --> 03:44.141
Dear Uberta, as lovely as ever.

03:46.185 --> 03:49.354
Oh. A nest. Heh-heh.

03:49.355 --> 03:53.400
And who might this strapping young man be?

03:53.401 --> 03:56.486
Young Prince Derek, no doubt.

03:56.487 --> 04:00.198
Welcome to our fair kingdom, dear William.

04:00.199 --> 04:03.870
And to you, young princess.

04:08.958 --> 04:10.585
Go on, Derek.

04:11.711 --> 04:13.962
Dear, go on.

04:13.963 --> 04:15.798
- Mother.
- Derek.

04:18.718 --> 04:23.263
Hello, Princess Odette.
I'm very pleased to meet you.

04:23.264 --> 04:25.975
Pleased to meet you, Prince Derek.

04:26.559 --> 04:28.102
Ah, ah, ah.

04:35.735 --> 04:36.985
Yuck!

04:36.986 --> 04:40.322
DEREK:
<i>♪ I can't believe I'm stuck with her all summer ♪</i>

04:40.323 --> 04:43.992
<i>♪ I'll bet she doesn't wrestle, hunt or box ♪</i>

04:43.993 --> 04:47.495
ODETTE: ♪ <i>He looks conceited ♪
- ♪ What a total bummer ♪</i>

04:47.496 --> 04:50.498
BOTH:
<i>♪ If I get lucky, I'll get chickenpox ♪</i>

04:50.499 --> 04:54.169
- ♪ So happy you could come ♪
- ♪ So happy to be here ♪

04:54.170 --> 04:57.505
BOTH:
<i>♪ How I'd like to run ♪</i>

04:57.506 --> 05:00.675
- ♪ This is not my idea ♪
- ♪ This isn't my idea ♪

05:00.676 --> 05:01.969
BOTH:
♪ Of fun ♪

05:04.972 --> 05:08.516
♪ The children seem to get along quite nicely ♪

05:08.517 --> 05:11.978
♪ We'll join our lands if this arrangement clicks ♪

05:11.979 --> 05:15.023
♪ My dear King William
That's my point precisely ♪

05:15.024 --> 05:18.276
- ♪ It's such good parenting ♪
- ♪ And politics ♪

05:18.277 --> 05:22.030
- ♪ So happy we agree ♪
- ♪ I think we've got a deal ♪

05:22.031 --> 05:25.784
UBERTA:
♪ Derek's quite a catch ♪

05:25.785 --> 05:28.828
♪ This is my idea ♪

05:28.829 --> 05:30.121
BOTH:
♪ Of a match ♪

05:30.122 --> 05:33.208
Heh-heh. And such fun.

05:33.209 --> 05:35.211
[♪♪♪]

05:47.807 --> 05:54.562
♪ Good heavens, child, don't dawdle
We can't keep Derek waiting ♪

05:54.563 --> 05:59.068
♪ I haven't packed or washed my hair
And, Father, I get seasick ♪

06:00.111 --> 06:06.741
♪ They soon will be arriving
Is that respect you're showing? ♪

06:06.742 --> 06:10.997
♪ If you make me kiss her hand again
I swear I'm gonna be sick ♪

06:12.707 --> 06:15.917
♪ One day Prince Derek will be her intended ♪

06:15.918 --> 06:18.170
UBERTA:
Heh-heh. Splendid.

06:21.257 --> 06:24.759
DEREK: ♪ <i>We've tried all summer
But we just can't lose her ♪</i>

06:24.760 --> 06:28.263
ODETTE: Hey, fellas, wait up!
BROM: Quick, put on some speed.

06:28.264 --> 06:29.973
DEREK: ♪ When picking teams ♪
BROM: ♪ Or friends ♪

06:29.974 --> 06:31.599
♪ I'd never choose her ♪

06:31.600 --> 06:34.769
♪ You'd think she'd take a hint and learn to read ♪

06:34.770 --> 06:38.857
- ♪ This really isn't fair ♪
BOTH: ♪ We really couldn't care ♪

06:38.858 --> 06:42.110
ODETTE:
<i>♪ Boys, it's all or none ♪</i>

06:42.111 --> 06:43.695
♪ This is not my idea ♪

06:43.696 --> 06:46.741
BOTH: ♪ This isn't my idea ♪
ALL: ♪ Of fun ♪

06:47.533 --> 06:48.367
[GRUNTS]

06:49.160 --> 06:52.454
CHORUS:
♪ Long before they met ♪

06:52.455 --> 06:57.375
♪ Derek and Odette ♪

06:57.376 --> 07:01.838
♪ Were destined to be wedded ♪

07:01.839 --> 07:04.799
♪ However anyone could see ♪

07:04.800 --> 07:08.595
♪ The only point on which they didn't disagree ♪

07:08.596 --> 07:12.682
♪ Was that the very thought of summertime ♪

07:12.683 --> 07:16.562
♪ Was dreaded ♪

07:20.816 --> 07:23.818
DEREK:
<i>♪ She tries to talk me into playing dress-up ♪</i>

07:23.819 --> 07:27.073
♪ She's always flirting with the castle guards ♪

07:27.740 --> 07:31.284
♪ I think you really sort of like her, fess up ♪

07:31.285 --> 07:33.828
DEREK:
<i>♪ I'd like her better if she'd lose at cards ♪</i>

07:33.829 --> 07:37.499
- ♪ Four sevens and a 10 ♪
- ♪ I think I've won again ♪

07:37.500 --> 07:41.002
BOTH:
♪ Every time she's won ♪

07:41.003 --> 07:45.549
- ♪ This is my idea of fun ♪
- ♪ This isn't my idea of fun ♪

07:51.305 --> 07:58.019
CHORUS: ♪ We need a royal wedding
I'd love to be invited ♪

07:58.020 --> 08:03.483
♪ At least we'd get a holiday
To rest our plows and axes ♪

08:03.484 --> 08:10.365
♪ Someday these two will marry
Two lands will be united ♪

08:10.366 --> 08:14.703
♪ And with some luck their marriage
May result in lower taxes ♪

08:16.080 --> 08:21.376
WILLIAM: ♪ <i>What if Odette doesn't go for the merger? ♪</i>
UBERTA: ♪ <i>Urge her ♪</i>

08:21.377 --> 08:22.628
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

08:24.922 --> 08:31.803
BOTH: ♪ For as long as I remember
We've been told we'd someday wed ♪

08:31.804 --> 08:35.515
♪ Every June until September ♪

08:35.515 --> 08:38.768
♪ All their pushing and annoying hints ♪

08:38.769 --> 08:41.313
♪ I've got bruises with their fingerprints ♪

08:42.273 --> 08:44.984
DEREK:
<i>♪ I can do much better, I am sure ♪</i>

08:45.943 --> 08:51.657
ODETTE:
<i>♪ He's so immature ♪</i>

08:55.161 --> 08:59.498
<i>♪ I see him smiling and my knees start buckling ♪</i>

09:00.499 --> 09:05.753
<i>♪ I see inside him and my doubts are gone ♪</i>

09:05.754 --> 09:10.009
DEREK:
<i>♪ She started out as such an ugly duckling ♪</i>

09:11.051 --> 09:15.430
<i>♪ And somehow suddenly became a swan ♪</i>

09:15.431 --> 09:20.894
- ♪ So happy to be here ♪
- ♪ Till now I never knew ♪

09:20.895 --> 09:26.733
BOTH:
♪ It is you I've been dreaming of ♪

09:26.734 --> 09:29.152
DEREK:
<i>♪ This is my idea ♪</i>

09:29.153 --> 09:31.362
ODETTE:
<i>♪ This is my idea ♪</i>

09:31.363 --> 09:35.241
BOTH: ♪ What a good idea
Such a charming and romantic notion ♪

09:35.242 --> 09:40.121
CHORUS:
♪ This is my idea, such a good idea ♪

09:40.122 --> 09:43.166
♪ Such a powerful and magic potion ♪

09:43.167 --> 09:48.379
♪ This is exactly my idea ♪

09:48.380 --> 09:53.469
♪ Of love ♪

09:56.805 --> 09:58.807
[♪♪♪]

10:11.820 --> 10:14.572
ODETTE:
<i>♪ This is my idea ♪</i>

10:14.573 --> 10:17.408
DEREK:
<i>♪ This is my idea ♪</i>

10:17.409 --> 10:21.913
BOTH:
<i>♪ This is my idea ♪</i>

10:21.914 --> 10:28.170
<i>♪ Of love ♪♪</i>

10:39.974 --> 10:41.516
Arrange the marriage.

10:41.517 --> 10:42.685
[UBERTA SQUEALS]

10:43.352 --> 10:45.354
[APPLAUSE]

10:51.235 --> 10:52.111
Wait.

10:55.864 --> 11:00.953
What? You're all I ever wanted.
You're beautiful.

11:01.620 --> 11:05.957
- Thank you. But what else?
- What else?

11:05.958 --> 11:08.043
Is beauty all that matters to you?

11:08.502 --> 11:09.878
[CLEARS THROAT]

11:12.589 --> 11:14.215
UBERTA:
Derek?

11:14.216 --> 11:15.634
What else?

11:16.468 --> 11:19.012
I... Uh...

11:19.013 --> 11:20.888
What else is there?

11:20.889 --> 11:22.141
[IMITATES BUZZER]

11:24.226 --> 11:26.228
[♪♪♪]

11:30.733 --> 11:34.486
We tried, Uberta.
No one can say we didn't try.

11:36.613 --> 11:39.324
- Say goodbye, Odette.
- Goodbye.

11:39.325 --> 11:42.244
- Goodbye...?
- Prince Derek.

11:43.537 --> 11:45.331
- Mother.
- Derek.

11:46.332 --> 11:47.750
Goodbye, princess.

11:59.678 --> 12:02.638
All these years of planning...

12:02.639 --> 12:04.975
wasted!

12:10.314 --> 12:12.316
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

12:15.361 --> 12:20.114
"What else is there?" She says,
"Is beauty all that matters?"

12:20.115 --> 12:23.868
And you say, "What else is there?"

12:23.869 --> 12:25.913
It was dumb, I know.

12:26.789 --> 12:31.794
You should write a book: <i>How to Offend
Women in Five Syllables or Less.</i>

12:32.336 --> 12:34.797
Heh-heh. Your turn, Prince Derek.

12:35.339 --> 12:37.299
DEREK:
I didn't know what else to say.

12:38.342 --> 12:42.553
- You lost your queen, Derek.
- That's twice in one day.

12:42.554 --> 12:47.058
Think. You must see something
other than Odette's beauty.

12:47.059 --> 12:50.353
Ha! Of course I do, Rogers. She's like...

12:50.354 --> 12:53.523
You know. And how about...?

12:53.524 --> 12:55.274
And then...

12:55.275 --> 12:56.151
I mean, right?

12:58.904 --> 13:00.948
I don't know how to say it.

13:02.199 --> 13:07.204
I'll prove it to her.
I'll prove my love. Checkmate.

13:08.497 --> 13:09.705
Huh?

13:09.706 --> 13:11.708
[♪♪♪]

13:17.381 --> 13:19.549
Today's the day, Willie.

13:19.550 --> 13:25.639
Everything you own,
everything you love will be mine.

13:27.391 --> 13:30.560
I just don't understand.

13:30.561 --> 13:33.981
What else did you want him to say?

13:34.648 --> 13:39.402
I need to know that he
loves me for just being me.

13:39.403 --> 13:41.321
MAN:
Whoa! Whoa.

13:45.534 --> 13:47.827
[♪♪♪]

13:47.828 --> 13:49.079
Stay inside, Odette.

13:56.170 --> 13:58.422
[ALL GASPING]

14:07.306 --> 14:08.932
It's King William's captain.

14:09.391 --> 14:10.392
We...

14:11.768 --> 14:16.189
We were attacked. A great animal.

14:16.190 --> 14:19.775
- Odette.
- Derek, wait!

14:19.776 --> 14:21.778
[♪♪♪]

14:28.535 --> 14:29.661
Odette!

14:32.164 --> 14:33.290
Odette?

14:34.500 --> 14:35.751
Odette!

14:37.586 --> 14:40.088
[♪♪♪]

14:41.173 --> 14:43.800
[WILLIAM PANTING]

14:45.010 --> 14:46.469
King William.

14:46.470 --> 14:47.553
Derek...

14:47.554 --> 14:48.596
[GROANS]

14:48.597 --> 14:50.515
Who did this?

14:50.516 --> 14:55.436
It came so quickly. A great animal.

14:55.437 --> 14:57.021
Where is Odette?

14:57.022 --> 15:02.443
Listen to me, Derek.
It's not what it seems.

15:02.444 --> 15:04.862
It's not what it seems.

15:04.863 --> 15:08.366
What's not? Where is Odette?

15:08.367 --> 15:10.953
Odette is...

15:12.204 --> 15:18.627
Odette is... gone.

15:23.632 --> 15:26.093
Odette!

15:35.894 --> 15:37.896
[♪♪♪]

16:11.930 --> 16:16.017
Now, don't let my little
spell make you sad, Odette,

16:16.018 --> 16:18.604
it doesn't even last the whole day.

16:19.062 --> 16:21.398
As soon as the moon comes up...

16:32.951 --> 16:36.454
And that's how it works every night.

16:36.455 --> 16:41.668
You have to be on the lake, of course.
And when the moonlight touches your wings...

16:42.169 --> 16:47.757
Now, look, Odette, this sort of thing
doesn't give me any pleasure.

16:47.758 --> 16:50.384
Well, maybe a teensy bit.

16:50.385 --> 16:54.889
But what I really want
is your father's kingdom.

16:54.890 --> 16:57.308
Take it, then. You have enough power.

16:57.309 --> 17:00.227
Nah, tried that already.

17:00.228 --> 17:05.567
Once you steal something,
you spend your whole life fighting to keep it.

17:06.859 --> 17:12.574
But if I marry the only
heir to the throne...

17:13.950 --> 17:20.330
we'll rule your father's kingdom together, legally.
King and queen. You know.

17:20.332 --> 17:21.415
Never.

17:22.501 --> 17:24.251
ROTHBART:
Where are you going?

17:24.252 --> 17:28.840
As soon as moonlight leaves the lake,
you'll turn back into a swan,

17:29.675 --> 17:31.510
no matter where you are.

17:33.095 --> 17:35.347
[CRYING]

17:43.605 --> 17:45.147
[♪♪♪]

17:45.148 --> 17:49.068
- The musicians are not happy.
DEREK: I know, but I have to practice.

17:49.069 --> 17:51.612
Oh, no complaints here.

17:51.613 --> 17:55.741
I think it's going to be loads of... fun.

17:55.742 --> 17:58.662
DEREK: The great animal is never
gonna give her up without a fight.

17:59.079 --> 18:01.330
You're not still thinking she's alive?

18:01.331 --> 18:05.084
When I find the great animal,
Rogers, I'll find Odette.

18:05.085 --> 18:10.506
Oh, Derek, you've looked everywhere.
She's not coming back.

18:10.507 --> 18:14.218
- The whole kingdom knows that.
- The whole kingdom's wrong.

18:14.219 --> 18:18.306
Odette's alive, and I'm gonna find her.
Ready, Brom?

18:18.682 --> 18:19.850
No peeking.

18:20.684 --> 18:22.978
Animals, assemble!

18:23.478 --> 18:27.481
Lord Rogers, I must object.
We are musicians.

18:27.482 --> 18:30.651
The servants have the day off.
We had to use someone.

18:30.652 --> 18:36.157
- But I'm an artist, not a boar.
- Could have fooled me.

18:36.158 --> 18:38.952
Come on, guys. They're harmless.

18:41.747 --> 18:45.583
ALL: ♪ We are a band
And not a band of animals ♪

18:45.584 --> 18:49.170
♪ This masquerade
Is more than I can bear ♪

18:49.171 --> 18:53.591
♪ There goes my reputation
It's awful, this humiliation ♪

18:53.592 --> 18:56.970
♪ And I've the lion's share ♪

18:57.512 --> 19:01.933
Down on all fours, please,
and growl ferociously!

19:03.059 --> 19:05.936
Liven it up a bit!

19:05.937 --> 19:09.523
I want you to strike fear into my heart!

19:09.524 --> 19:10.691
[MAN ROARS]

19:10.692 --> 19:15.614
Not you, Wesley.
You're a rabbit, for heaven's sake.

19:18.492 --> 19:21.161
Archers. Ready.

19:22.204 --> 19:23.622
Set.

19:25.207 --> 19:26.124
Go!

19:39.554 --> 19:41.640
- Duck.
- Yes?

19:43.058 --> 19:43.975
[CHUCKLES]

19:52.901 --> 19:54.653
- Duck!
- What?

19:55.529 --> 19:59.073
CHORUS:
♪ Day after day, all the prince ever does ♪

19:59.074 --> 20:02.619
♪ Is practice, practice, practice ♪

20:03.161 --> 20:06.872
♪ Thinking of her and the way that it was ♪

20:06.873 --> 20:09.960
♪ Practice, practice, practice ♪

20:10.836 --> 20:13.755
♪ He's not happy till he has attacked us ♪

20:15.173 --> 20:17.259
[♪♪♪]

20:19.135 --> 20:20.929
[YELLING]

20:21.680 --> 20:22.930
Twelve seconds.

20:22.931 --> 20:27.936
CHORUS: ♪ Day after day all the prince ever does
Practice, practice, practice ♪

20:28.854 --> 20:34.400
♪ Thinking of her and the way that it was
Practice, practice, practice ♪

20:34.401 --> 20:36.193
♪ If we had refused
He would have sacked us ♪

20:36.194 --> 20:37.361
Five seconds!

20:37.362 --> 20:39.321
- ♪ So we face a life of target practice ♪
- Three!

20:39.322 --> 20:41.991
- Two!
- ♪ Practice, practice, practice! ♪♪

20:41.992 --> 20:46.161
Time! Animals, assemble for counting.

20:46.162 --> 20:48.831
Uh-huh. Very good, very good.

20:48.832 --> 20:53.669
You scored plenty of
five-pointers, that's for sure.

20:53.670 --> 20:56.630
Sorry, Hans.
Why don't you take a few days off?

20:56.631 --> 21:01.886
Moose are worth two points.
Sixteen hits, a total of 32.

21:01.887 --> 21:06.682
Ten seven-pointers and 14 three-pointers.

21:06.683 --> 21:10.519
For a total of... 298!

21:10.520 --> 21:12.438
Well done, Derek.

21:12.439 --> 21:14.524
Now, Bromley, let's see. For you...

21:15.275 --> 21:19.946
Zero, and zero, and
nothing, and nil, and zip.

21:22.073 --> 21:24.575
And last but not least,

21:24.576 --> 21:29.623
the elusive 100-point white rabbit...

21:32.250 --> 21:36.337
BROM: I believe that's 300, Rogers.
- Good shooting, Brom.

21:36.338 --> 21:40.926
Well? Write it down. Three hundred to 298.

21:41.301 --> 21:45.138
Oh, but wait just a moment, Rogers.

21:48.183 --> 21:49.267
Sorry, Brom.

21:49.851 --> 21:50.935
[CHUCKLES]

21:50.936 --> 21:54.772
You're a great marksman, Derek.
One of the best.

21:54.773 --> 21:56.941
But it takes more than good aim.

21:56.942 --> 22:00.861
It takes courage. That's my forte.

22:00.862 --> 22:04.823
Well, then, how about a quick
round of "Catch and Fire"?

22:04.824 --> 22:06.909
[STAMMERING]

22:06.910 --> 22:09.328
Catch and fire? You mean, me?

22:09.329 --> 22:11.121
You're the only one with enough

22:11.122 --> 22:13.917
[STUTTERING]
c-courage.

22:17.295 --> 22:20.547
ROGERS: Are you sure you're all right?
BROM: Mm-hm.

22:20.548 --> 22:22.717
Fine, I'm fine.

22:23.969 --> 22:26.930
Oh! Too tight. Too tight.

22:27.263 --> 22:30.182
Whoops. So sorry.

22:30.183 --> 22:31.601
DEREK:
Ready?

22:33.019 --> 22:34.228
[BROM STAMMERS]

22:34.229 --> 22:35.188
He's ready.

22:36.856 --> 22:41.235
Remember now, aim for the heart.

22:41.236 --> 22:43.697
Right between the shoulders.

22:46.116 --> 22:48.034
[♪♪♪]

22:54.708 --> 22:56.543
Oh, please, oh, please, oh, please.

22:59.587 --> 23:03.216
Come on, Brom. Hold it steady.

23:03.758 --> 23:07.511
Oh, please, oh, please. Oh, please.

23:07.512 --> 23:08.596
Now!

23:16.438 --> 23:17.689
Whew!

23:18.064 --> 23:23.444
Fifty-two out of 52! Well done, Derek!

23:23.445 --> 23:25.904
Extraordinary courage, man.

23:25.905 --> 23:30.785
Just think, one inch lower
and that arrow would have...

23:36.875 --> 23:42.839
Don't lose hope, Odette.
Wherever you are, I'm gonna find you.

23:46.259 --> 23:48.261
[♪♪♪]

23:49.429 --> 23:50.596
[MAN 1 CHUCKLES]

23:50.597 --> 23:52.890
MAN 2 [IN FRENCH ACCENT]:
Quiet! I cannot concentrate.

23:52.891 --> 23:58.228
You've come up with some dumb ideas, Jean-Bob,
but this one is a doozy.

23:58.229 --> 24:04.526
Ha! Go ahead and laugh. I'll get her to kiss me.
And when she does...

24:04.527 --> 24:11.408
And when she does, poof. You'll change into a prince.
I know, I know, you've told me.

24:11.409 --> 24:15.329
Why don't you just give her these flowers?
These are pretty.

24:15.330 --> 24:21.919
Ha! What a love-dunce.
I don't want these flowers, I must have those.

24:21.920 --> 24:25.839
When she learns that I have
risked my life for them,

24:25.840 --> 24:28.342
the kissing will not stop.

24:28.343 --> 24:31.970
- And then you'll change into a prince?
- Precisely.

24:31.971 --> 24:37.226
- Mind if I point out a problem?
- I don't take advice from peasants.

24:37.227 --> 24:38.478
Suit yourself.

24:41.773 --> 24:47.987
Flowers, kiss, concentration.
Flowers, kiss, concentration.

24:49.072 --> 24:52.574
Just curious, how are you gonna get back?

24:52.575 --> 24:54.744
[GULPS, THEN SCREAMS]

25:02.544 --> 25:04.045
[SCREAMS]

25:05.713 --> 25:07.298
Hurry, hurry!

25:09.676 --> 25:13.471
Move up! Move up! No, not that.

25:14.347 --> 25:15.430
Close!

25:15.431 --> 25:16.808
[JEAN-BOB SCREAMS]

25:19.185 --> 25:24.231
Grab me! Grab me! Hold my arm! Hold my leg!

25:24.232 --> 25:26.818
Hold my-- Hold it, hold it, hold it.

25:28.069 --> 25:29.988
Oh, thank you, Odette.

25:31.447 --> 25:33.949
Thank you. Let me have that.

25:33.950 --> 25:36.161
Silence, you savages.

25:36.828 --> 25:38.621
Ha-ha! Ungh!

25:39.414 --> 25:40.915
Are you all right, Jean-Bob?

25:41.416 --> 25:42.499
Jean-Bob?

25:42.500 --> 25:45.752
<i>Oui, oui, oui,</i> Odette. Yes, I'm all right.

25:45.753 --> 25:49.173
- What in the world were you trying to do?
- He thought that if--

25:49.174 --> 25:54.219
Shush! I wanted to get
those flowers for you.

25:54.220 --> 25:56.555
You're being sneaky again, Jean-Bob.

25:56.556 --> 26:02.227
- What sneaky? You deserve a nice bouquet.
- And you deserve a kiss.

26:02.228 --> 26:03.896
Well, all right.

26:03.897 --> 26:07.900
- You know I'm under a spell.
- But my kiss will break the spell.

26:07.901 --> 26:10.068
Give it up, Jean-Bob.

26:10.069 --> 26:12.905
I can only kiss the man I love.

26:12.906 --> 26:17.159
- And then he--
- Must make a vow of everlasting love.

26:17.160 --> 26:18.911
And prove it to the world.

26:18.912 --> 26:23.832
What do you think I was doing with the flowers
and the alligators going chomp-chomp?

26:23.833 --> 26:27.754
- Speed, make him understand.
- I'm only a turtle.

26:28.963 --> 26:34.259
♪ If I could break this spell
I'd run to him today ♪

26:34.260 --> 26:39.848
♪ And somehow I know
He's on his way to me ♪

26:39.849 --> 26:46.855
♪ Derek, you and I were meant to be ♪

26:46.856 --> 26:52.110
♪ For longer than forever ♪

26:52.111 --> 26:56.698
♪ I'll hold you in my heart ♪

26:56.699 --> 27:00.869
♪ It's almost like you're here with me ♪

27:00.870 --> 27:05.123
♪ Although we're far apart ♪

27:05.124 --> 27:10.003
♪ For longer than forever ♪

27:10.004 --> 27:13.966
♪ As constant as a star ♪

27:13.967 --> 27:15.884
♪ I close my eyes ♪

27:15.885 --> 27:22.432
♪ And I am where you are ♪

27:22.433 --> 27:29.439
ODETTE: ♪ <i>Sure as the dawn brings the sunrise
We've an unshakable bond ♪</i>

27:29.440 --> 27:35.654
DEREK:
<i>♪ Destined to last for a lifetime and beyond ♪</i>

27:35.655 --> 27:40.909
♪ For longer than forever ♪

27:40.910 --> 27:45.580
♪ I swear that I'll be true ♪

27:45.581 --> 27:50.127
- ♪ I've made an everlasting vow ♪
- ♪ An everlasting vow ♪

27:50.128 --> 27:54.506
BOTH:
♪ To find a way to you ♪

27:54.507 --> 27:59.386
♪ For longer than forever ♪

27:59.387 --> 28:03.974
♪ Like no love ever known ♪

28:03.975 --> 28:05.517
ODETTE:
♪ And with your love ♪

28:05.518 --> 28:12.525
BOTH:
♪ I'll never be alone ♪

28:14.027 --> 28:19.239
♪ For longer than forever ♪

28:19.240 --> 28:24.619
♪ Much stronger than forever ♪

28:24.620 --> 28:26.705
♪ And with your love ♪

28:26.706 --> 28:33.713
♪ I'll never be alone ♪♪

28:44.974 --> 28:46.684
[SHIVERING]

28:47.310 --> 28:48.227
Oh!

28:50.438 --> 28:53.983
- You think he's dead?
- No, it's just his wing, I think.

28:54.359 --> 28:56.568
- Strange-looking bird.
- Ooh!

28:56.569 --> 29:01.574
Poor fellow. He must be in a lot of pain.
You'd better hold him.

29:02.909 --> 29:04.243
- Ooh!
- Ready.

29:06.496 --> 29:07.830
[YELPS]

29:10.375 --> 29:14.086
Hello. This is your wake-up call.

29:14.087 --> 29:16.672
[GRUNTING]

29:18.007 --> 29:23.261
It takes more than a pair of pond punks
to keep Puffin down. Hiyah!

29:23.262 --> 29:26.098
Wait. I'm your friend.

29:26.099 --> 29:31.603
If you were me friend,
how come you have an arrow in your hand? Huh?

29:31.604 --> 29:35.024
- Yes, the exact kind of arrow I have--
- Heh-heh.

29:35.983 --> 29:37.068
Um...

29:37.527 --> 29:39.778
I took it out while you were laying there.

29:39.779 --> 29:42.948
You mean, you had a chance to
"krkk" and instead you "fft"?

29:42.949 --> 29:44.117
Uh-huh.

29:44.450 --> 29:50.205
Madam, I apologize. Me name is Puffin.
Lieutenant Puffin.

29:50.206 --> 29:55.378
It's a pleasure, Lieutenant Puffin.
I'm Odette, Princess Odette.

29:57.505 --> 30:02.385
And these are my best friends in the whole world.
Mr. Lorenzo Trudgealong...

30:02.760 --> 30:06.138
- Friends call me Speed.
ODETTE: And Jean-Bob.

30:06.139 --> 30:11.977
I have no friends, only servants.
They call me "Your Highness."

30:11.978 --> 30:13.896
Thinks he's a prince.

30:14.355 --> 30:15.272
[WHISTLES]

30:15.273 --> 30:19.944
Ahem. I owe you, princess.
And I intend on staying until me debt is paid.

30:20.445 --> 30:24.030
I don't think there's much you can do.
He has me under a spell.

30:24.031 --> 30:26.159
What? You mean, a magical...?

30:27.952 --> 30:29.954
[♪♪♪]

30:40.590 --> 30:46.136
Your knight in shining armor has come
to set you free. Heh-heh.

30:46.137 --> 30:48.513
Let me at him. Let me at him. I'll...

30:48.514 --> 30:50.098
[GRUNTING]

30:50.099 --> 30:51.475
Chill.

30:51.476 --> 30:55.896
All it takes is just one little word.

30:55.897 --> 30:58.648
Will you... marry me?

30:58.649 --> 31:01.651
- Every night you ask the same question.
- No, no.

31:01.652 --> 31:05.238
- And every night I give you the same answer.
- Don't!

31:05.239 --> 31:09.993
- I'll die first.
- You're really starting to bug me.

31:09.994 --> 31:15.040
- I should think you'd be used to it by now.
- That's it! Just keep pushing it.

31:15.041 --> 31:18.668
But someday I'm gonna boil over!

31:18.669 --> 31:22.006
Go ahead, then! But I'll never
give you my father's kingdom.

31:22.507 --> 31:23.633
[GRUNTING]

31:24.759 --> 31:28.178
I was hoping you'd say you'd be mine,

31:28.179 --> 31:34.477
but it looks as if you need
another day to think about it.

31:35.102 --> 31:36.938
[LAUGHING]

31:37.355 --> 31:38.355
No.

31:38.356 --> 31:39.941
[LAUGHTER CONTINUES]

31:44.862 --> 31:46.864
[♪♪♪]

32:01.295 --> 32:02.380
[SIGHS]

32:03.047 --> 32:04.215
Princess?

32:10.513 --> 32:15.016
Beautiful. Simply beautiful.

32:15.017 --> 32:20.480
Soon Derek will be married,
and the kingdom will have a king again.

32:20.481 --> 32:25.652
I doubt it. Derek refuses to be king,
unless he finds Odette.

32:25.653 --> 32:30.699
Oh, poppycock. All that will
change at tomorrow night's ball.

32:30.700 --> 32:33.285
They're all coming to the ball. Ha-ha-ha!

32:33.286 --> 32:35.412
Every princess is coming.

32:35.413 --> 32:37.038
[LAUGHS]

32:37.039 --> 32:40.041
Oh, goody, oh, my. Oh, this is wonderful.

32:40.042 --> 32:44.796
You see, Rogers.
One of these is bound to change his mind.

32:44.797 --> 32:48.133
Oh, absolutely... not.

32:48.134 --> 32:52.971
- Do not lose one.
- Oh, no. No. No, no.

32:52.972 --> 32:55.807
Where is Derek?
Oh, never mind, I know where he is,

32:55.808 --> 32:59.144
working on the mystery of the fat animal.

32:59.145 --> 33:04.233
- The great animal, Your Highness.
- Big, great. It's large and has fur.

33:05.735 --> 33:10.323
WILLIAM:
<i>Listen, Derek, it's not what it seems.</i>

33:11.616 --> 33:13.743
What did King William mean?

33:14.744 --> 33:16.954
[♪♪♪]

33:27.798 --> 33:34.596
It's not what it seems... Of course.
It's not what it seems.

33:34.597 --> 33:36.974
Now I'll find you, Odette.

33:38.559 --> 33:43.104
They're coming, Derek!
Oh, Derek, where are you going?

33:43.105 --> 33:46.983
- To find the great animal.
- Oh, wonderful.

33:46.984 --> 33:49.402
Just make sure you're here tomorrow night.

33:49.403 --> 33:50.321
Tomorrow night?

33:50.738 --> 33:52.280
[STAMMERS]

33:52.281 --> 33:53.323
The ball.

33:53.324 --> 33:55.576
Mother, I can't.

33:57.244 --> 34:00.498
Oh, please, Mother. Don't do the lip thing.

34:01.499 --> 34:04.501
If I leave now,
maybe I can be back in time.

34:04.502 --> 34:06.169
[EXCLAIMS]

34:06.170 --> 34:07.254
Thank you, darling.

34:07.922 --> 34:09.005
[UBERTA CHUCKLES]

34:09.005 --> 34:11.925
But please, Mother, don't turn it
into one of your beauty pageants.

34:11.926 --> 34:18.599
Oh! No, no, no. It's just a few
friends and their daughters.

34:19.684 --> 34:22.435
I want this to be big.

34:22.436 --> 34:24.896
Every princess must have
her own introduction.

34:24.897 --> 34:28.358
- But you said--
- Forget what I said.

34:28.359 --> 34:30.068
Now, send for the cooks.

34:30.069 --> 34:33.071
And tell the band to start rehearsing.

34:33.072 --> 34:37.449
And I want four footmen
for every carriage. Ha-ha!

34:37.451 --> 34:38.911
Maybe five.

34:40.788 --> 34:45.458
Let me get this straight.
Every night, when the moonlight leaves the lake, you...

34:47.585 --> 34:48.503
[HONKS]

34:48.504 --> 34:49.545
ODETTE:
Right.

34:49.547 --> 34:54.467
The following night, if I want to turn back into a human,
I have to be on the lake.

34:54.885 --> 34:59.222
Hmph. All she needs is a little moonlight.
Me, I have to be smooched.

34:59.223 --> 35:04.728
No fear. You fly to your prince,
we bring him back to the lake,

35:04.729 --> 35:08.565
the moon comes up,
you change into a princess, and:

35:08.566 --> 35:10.108
[HUMS "BRIDAL CHORUS"]

35:10.109 --> 35:11.651
Happily ever after.

35:11.652 --> 35:14.738
- How will I find him?
- You don't know where he is?

35:14.739 --> 35:16.740
I don't even know where I am.

35:16.741 --> 35:20.410
- I bet he does.
- Oh, that's a great idea.

35:20.411 --> 35:25.248
Just say, "Monsieur Rothbart, I'd like to leave now.
Do you have a map or something?"

35:25.249 --> 35:26.916
Ah! That's it.

35:26.917 --> 35:28.084
BOTH:
A map.

35:28.085 --> 35:30.628
- Ah!
- Let's do it.

35:30.629 --> 35:33.548
♪ We're off on a mission
We're tough, in good condition ♪

35:33.549 --> 35:35.133
- ♪ We're short ♪
- ♪ But standing tall ♪

35:35.134 --> 35:36.801
ALL:
♪ No fear! ♪

35:36.802 --> 35:40.096
ODETTE: ♪ There's danger around us ♪
- ♪ They'd hurt us if they found us ♪

35:40.097 --> 35:41.306
♪ Our backs are to the wall ♪

35:41.307 --> 35:42.724
ALL:
♪ No fear! ♪

35:42.725 --> 35:46.478
♪ 'Cause we have all the courage we require ♪

35:46.479 --> 35:49.564
♪ Take it from a frequent flyer ♪

35:49.565 --> 35:52.442
ALL:
♪ Try your luck, our plan will fly ♪

35:52.443 --> 35:53.778
ALL:
♪ No fear! ♪

35:55.529 --> 35:58.823
It's hanging on the wall
in the upper chamber.

35:58.824 --> 36:01.660
Odette can keep a lookout
while we get the map.

36:02.119 --> 36:04.788
- "We"?
- You're not going to help us?

36:04.789 --> 36:05.706
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

36:06.123 --> 36:09.167
♪ This plan if applied
Will be simply suicidal ♪

36:09.168 --> 36:12.170
- ♪ You'll be a sitting duck ♪
ALL: ♪ No fear! ♪

36:12.171 --> 36:15.590
♪ Suppose that I do this
Who knows if we'll live through this ♪

36:15.591 --> 36:17.175
♪ How about a kiss for luck? ♪

36:17.176 --> 36:18.176
ODETTE: ♪ No ♪
BOTH: ♪ Fear ♪

36:18.177 --> 36:24.682
♪ Our team is shy
One green webbed-footed volunteer ♪

36:24.683 --> 36:27.852
- ♪ No way, Jose, no chance ♪
- ♪ No choice ♪

36:27.853 --> 36:29.187
ALL:
♪ No fear ♪♪

36:29.188 --> 36:31.607
No, stop it! Stop it! No!

36:32.149 --> 36:34.151
[♪♪♪]

36:38.572 --> 36:42.409
- All right, quickly.
- Easy for you to say.

36:43.118 --> 36:43.994
Ouch.

36:46.247 --> 36:51.502
Whenever I have to do something quick,
I always bring a turtle.

36:54.672 --> 36:57.090
I think I pulled a muscle.

36:57.091 --> 37:02.470
I'm gonna die! I know it!
I'm on a dangerous mission with a lame turtle.

37:02.471 --> 37:05.349
You're going to get us all killed.

37:13.440 --> 37:15.108
Beat ya.

37:15.109 --> 37:21.447
ALL: ♪ We will take any dare
That the other side'll dare to dream up ♪

37:21.448 --> 37:27.121
♪ We play tough, we play fair
But we're sure to win because we'll team up ♪♪

37:29.748 --> 37:31.708
- Ah!
- Yikes.

37:31.709 --> 37:32.960
Head for the door.

37:34.712 --> 37:36.297
[CACKLES]

37:37.006 --> 37:40.425
All right, Jean-Bob goes deep.
Speed gets the hand-off.

37:40.426 --> 37:41.342
Ready?

37:41.343 --> 37:42.261
ALL:
Break.

37:42.595 --> 37:44.054
Set, hut-hut.

37:47.808 --> 37:49.393
I'm open, I'm open.

37:51.562 --> 37:52.521
[CHUCKLES]

37:55.232 --> 37:57.985
- Get that map.
- Ah!

37:59.570 --> 38:01.322
Ha! Uh-huh!

38:02.406 --> 38:04.449
[SCREAMING]

38:04.450 --> 38:05.742
Saved ya.

38:05.743 --> 38:07.244
Ah!

38:07.703 --> 38:08.621
Reach.

38:10.497 --> 38:13.042
Hey, batter, batter, batter.

38:17.171 --> 38:19.381
Oh, the crowd's going wild.

38:21.467 --> 38:22.551
CHORUS:
<i>♪ No fear! ♪</i>

38:28.307 --> 38:29.807
<i>♪ No fear! ♪</i>

38:29.808 --> 38:35.813
<i>♪ If only one of us knew how to steer ♪</i>

38:35.814 --> 38:37.732
PUFFIN: ♪ Get a grip ♪
SPEED: ♪ Get set ♪

38:37.733 --> 38:39.150
PUFFIN:
♪ That's our best bet ♪

38:39.151 --> 38:40.610
- ♪ No brakes ♪
SPEED: ♪ No sweat ♪

38:40.611 --> 38:42.111
PUFFIN:
♪ And no regret ♪

38:42.112 --> 38:43.863
- ♪ We're dead ♪
- ♪ Not yet ♪

38:43.864 --> 38:45.950
♪ Oh, no, no ♪

38:47.576 --> 38:49.328
Save me.

38:55.584 --> 38:59.213
CHORUS:
<i>♪ No fear! ♪♪</i>

39:00.214 --> 39:03.175
There's Derek's kingdom. When do we leave?

39:11.058 --> 39:14.186
- It's a mouse.
- The great animal.

39:14.561 --> 39:18.606
Ha-ha. A tad small, wouldn't you say?

39:18.607 --> 39:22.861
Yeah, until it changes into this.

39:24.279 --> 39:27.115
An animal that can change its shape.

39:27.116 --> 39:29.659
A harmless creature approaches,

39:29.660 --> 39:33.205
then suddenly it's too late.

39:33.872 --> 39:38.043
- You mean, it could be anything?
- Anything.

39:40.629 --> 39:41.964
[SHOUTS]

39:44.299 --> 39:48.177
Odette, I apologize for
the way I've been acting.

39:48.178 --> 39:49.637
It's all right, Jean-Bob.

39:49.638 --> 39:56.227
No, no. This Derek is very important to you,
and all I can do is think of myself.

39:56.228 --> 39:57.895
Everyone does that.

39:57.896 --> 40:01.482
Please, Odette, don't make this more difficult
than it already is.

40:01.483 --> 40:05.737
- Accept my apology, please.
- Okay. I accept.

40:05.738 --> 40:08.698
Good. Now we can kiss and make up.

40:08.699 --> 40:10.074
BOTH:
Jean-Bob.

40:10.075 --> 40:11.951
What? What did I say? What? What?

40:11.952 --> 40:13.370
PUFFIN:
Ten-hut.

40:14.038 --> 40:16.289
It is zero hour, troops.

40:16.290 --> 40:19.709
- Odette, prepare for takeoff.
- Right.

40:19.710 --> 40:23.838
PUFFIN: The rest of you have your assignments.
Is everyone ready?

40:23.839 --> 40:25.965
Ready for action, sir.

40:25.966 --> 40:27.550
How about you, Jean-Bob?

40:27.551 --> 40:29.594
[♪♪♪]

40:29.595 --> 40:30.596
Jean-Bob?

40:33.140 --> 40:37.518
- Highness.
<i>- Oui,</i> I am ready.

40:37.519 --> 40:38.520
Take off!

40:40.481 --> 40:43.691
Good luck. Have a nice flight.

40:43.692 --> 40:50.364
Remember, if anything happens to her,
I'll have you whipped, flogged,

40:50.365 --> 40:51.699
put on the rack,

40:51.700 --> 40:57.456
and then have your back
legs fried in butter!

40:58.749 --> 41:00.751
[♪♪♪]

41:08.842 --> 41:12.386
DEREK:
He's in here, Brom. I can feel it.

41:12.387 --> 41:15.431
BROM: How will you know the
great animal when you see it?

41:15.432 --> 41:16.725
DEREK:
I'll know.

41:17.434 --> 41:18.811
Better stay close.

41:19.812 --> 41:21.313
If you say so.

41:34.993 --> 41:37.996
Derek? Derek, where are you?

41:38.664 --> 41:41.333
- Shh, shh.
- Oh. Sorry. Heh.

41:43.252 --> 41:45.254
[♪♪♪]

42:10.946 --> 42:12.197
Derek?

42:13.907 --> 42:15.868
Oh! Oh! Oh! Derek!

42:17.661 --> 42:19.829
We'd better keep an eye out for hunters.

42:19.830 --> 42:21.539
[PUFFIN CHUCKLES]

42:21.540 --> 42:23.457
At ease, Odette.

42:23.458 --> 42:27.420
I can smell a human a mile away.

42:27.421 --> 42:31.465
- Ah! Where did that come from?
BROM: Derek!

42:31.466 --> 42:34.845
Ah! Derek. He's here.

42:35.888 --> 42:40.308
You will not lose control.
You will follow the plan as outlined.

42:40.309 --> 42:43.437
Acknowledge. Acknowle-- Ah!

42:44.688 --> 42:45.814
Odette!

42:53.822 --> 42:55.282
[BRANCH SNAPS]

42:59.411 --> 43:01.872
[BIRDS CAWING IN DISTANCE]

43:09.463 --> 43:10.297
Odette?

43:17.971 --> 43:23.393
I've got you now. Heh-heh.
Don't give me that innocent look.

43:23.852 --> 43:26.939
Change! Go ahead, change.

43:27.731 --> 43:29.608
I'm not afraid of you.

43:30.442 --> 43:31.276
[SQUEAKS]

43:31.735 --> 43:33.153
[YELLING]

43:43.372 --> 43:45.457
[♪♪♪]

43:45.874 --> 43:47.292
Ah! Derek.

43:52.839 --> 43:56.842
A swan? A swan.

43:56.843 --> 44:00.889
Of course. It's not what it seems.

44:02.474 --> 44:04.810
Just a little closer.

44:05.602 --> 44:08.939
Come on. Come on.

44:10.107 --> 44:10.941
Derek.

44:12.234 --> 44:13.944
This one's for Odette.

44:14.486 --> 44:16.405
Ah! Odette!

44:18.240 --> 44:20.242
[♪♪♪]

44:23.036 --> 44:25.956
Whew! Hoo. Oh, that was close.

44:27.082 --> 44:29.793
It's working, here he comes.

44:30.919 --> 44:33.672
Hey! Slow down. You're going to lose him.

44:36.800 --> 44:39.635
Slow down.

44:39.636 --> 44:42.514
- He's too close.
- Too close?

44:43.348 --> 44:45.767
He can't even see us anymore, let alone--

44:46.101 --> 44:48.270
Ah! Speed up, girl.

44:49.396 --> 44:52.023
- That boy of yours can move.
ODETTE: I told you.

44:52.024 --> 44:54.150
He's faster than you thought.

44:54.151 --> 44:57.988
Don't worry, Odette. I've been taught
what to do in this situation.

44:58.363 --> 44:59.197
Well?

45:00.198 --> 45:01.033
Puffin!

45:01.700 --> 45:02.825
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

45:02.826 --> 45:06.871
When the archer has you in his sights,
fly into the sun and use its light.

45:06.872 --> 45:08.373
Follow me!

45:12.252 --> 45:13.587
[CHUCKLES]

45:14.671 --> 45:19.384
What did I tell you, Odette?
All we have to do is stay in the sun.

45:24.264 --> 45:25.140
[GASPS]

45:28.060 --> 45:29.226
[ODETTE GASPS]

45:29.227 --> 45:32.147
All right, don't panic. Don't panic. Uh...

45:32.647 --> 45:34.065
[BOTH GASP]

45:34.066 --> 45:36.693
ODETTE: Puffin! Into the trees.
- Odette! Hurry!

45:42.616 --> 45:47.119
We'd better think of something quick,
or else we're dead ducks.

45:47.120 --> 45:52.751
Remember what the possum said:
When there's no escape, you have to play dead.

45:54.086 --> 45:58.382
Heh-heh. Gives it the right touch, yes?
Wait till I give you a...

46:00.634 --> 46:01.885
[THUD]

46:02.677 --> 46:04.221
[GRUNTING]

46:18.068 --> 46:19.236
[YELPS]

46:20.904 --> 46:24.824
Ha-ha! That'll put some
distance between us.

46:24.825 --> 46:26.827
[♪♪♪]

46:28.161 --> 46:30.162
No sign of them yet.

46:30.163 --> 46:35.502
- I hope that pudgy Puffin knows what he's doing.
- Incoming.

46:42.426 --> 46:44.845
Ha-ha! There they are.

46:52.561 --> 46:54.688
It's almost time, Odette. Look.

46:58.400 --> 47:01.193
- I can't do it.
- Well, you have to.

47:01.194 --> 47:03.029
He'll kill me, Puffin.

47:04.156 --> 47:07.534
You don't do it now,
you've lost your chance for life.

47:08.785 --> 47:09.870
All right.

47:11.621 --> 47:13.039
- I'll do it.
- Go.

47:18.795 --> 47:19.629
What?

47:21.047 --> 47:23.133
All right, come on, come on.

47:27.888 --> 47:28.805
[GASPS]

47:30.390 --> 47:31.558
Got ya.

47:33.727 --> 47:35.228
[CAWS]

47:38.523 --> 47:40.525
[♪♪♪]

47:55.707 --> 47:56.791
Hello, Derek.

48:06.885 --> 48:09.512
Oh, Derek, I've missed you so.

48:09.513 --> 48:12.181
No one believed me. But I knew.

48:12.182 --> 48:15.267
- You can't stay.
- Can't stay?

48:15.268 --> 48:17.937
No, I'll never let you
out of my sight again.

48:17.938 --> 48:20.314
- Listen to me, Derek.
ROTHBART: Odette.

48:20.315 --> 48:23.442
- Oh, no.
- Who is it? What's going on?

48:23.443 --> 48:25.277
- It's him.
- Who?

48:25.278 --> 48:27.863
- He has me under a spell.
- Who does?

48:27.864 --> 48:29.114
ROTHBART:
Odette!

48:29.115 --> 48:33.827
- Let him come. I'll--
- No. He has great power, you must go.

48:33.828 --> 48:36.413
- Then you're coming with me.
- I can't.

48:36.414 --> 48:39.083
When the moon sets,
I'll turn back into a swan.

48:39.084 --> 48:42.753
Please, Derek, you have to trust me. Go.

48:42.754 --> 48:45.256
There must be some way to break the spell.

48:45.257 --> 48:49.510
Oh, there is. You must make
a vow of everlasting love.

48:49.511 --> 48:51.720
I make it. It's all I've ever wanted.

48:51.721 --> 48:55.307
- You must prove it to the world.
- How? How?

48:55.308 --> 48:56.642
I don't know.

48:56.643 --> 48:59.187
ROTHBART: Odette?
- Go!

49:00.564 --> 49:04.817
The ball.
Tomorrow night, come to the castle.

49:04.818 --> 49:10.114
Before the whole world,
I will make a vow of everlasting love.

49:10.115 --> 49:14.535
ROTHBART: Odette!
- I'm coming! Go.

49:14.536 --> 49:18.539
- Tomorrow night.
- Yes, tomorrow night.

49:18.540 --> 49:19.624
Now go.

49:22.752 --> 49:26.964
Odette! Didn't you hear me calling?

49:26.965 --> 49:29.383
I... I...

49:29.384 --> 49:32.887
I thought I heard voices.

49:34.097 --> 49:37.391
- Odette, Odette.
- Voices?

49:37.392 --> 49:41.061
- Yes, voices.
- Well, I...

49:41.062 --> 49:42.313
You what?

49:42.314 --> 49:45.482
I've decided to become your queen.

49:45.483 --> 49:46.817
[ALL GASP]

49:46.818 --> 49:50.195
No. You mean...?

49:50.196 --> 49:54.408
Ha-ha. Odette, you've made me so happy.

49:54.409 --> 49:56.368
I'll be a good king, you'll see.

49:56.369 --> 50:01.207
I'll wear nice clothes,
and I'm gonna get my beard trimmed.

50:02.417 --> 50:05.962
Oh, you've made me so happy, Odette.

50:08.590 --> 50:14.763
By the way, you wouldn't happen to know
who this belongs to, would you?

50:16.014 --> 50:17.181
[JEAN-BOB YELPS]

50:17.182 --> 50:20.059
"Come to the ball.

50:20.060 --> 50:24.522
I will make a vow of everlasting love."

50:25.940 --> 50:27.233
[CACKLES]

50:27.859 --> 50:31.363
Thought you could fool Rothbart, did you?

50:32.947 --> 50:37.494
I will never be yours, you creature!

50:37.952 --> 50:42.539
- I will marry Prince Derek. And you cannot stop me.
- Oh...

50:42.540 --> 50:45.043
I hate to tell you this, Odette.

50:45.794 --> 50:50.881
But you won't be able to attend
the big ball tomorrow night.

50:50.882 --> 50:55.386
If you want to stop me,
you'll have to kill me.

50:55.387 --> 50:58.555
No. I don't think so.

50:58.556 --> 51:01.809
You see, you've forgotten
one very important thing.

51:01.810 --> 51:07.231
Tomorrow night... there is no moon.

51:07.232 --> 51:08.483
[CACKLING]

51:10.735 --> 51:11.986
[CRYING]

51:27.335 --> 51:30.922
No matter what they do,
I'm always one step ahead.

51:31.381 --> 51:35.427
On the other hand,
Prince Derek's vow could ruin everything.

51:36.636 --> 51:41.390
- I'm going to have to deal with him. But how?
- Hmm.

51:41.391 --> 51:47.021
The vow. I'll get Derek to offer
his vow to the wrong princess.

51:48.523 --> 51:52.694
That's it. Ha-ha.
I'll make you look like Odette.

51:53.153 --> 51:57.406
Well, that's gonna take a lot of
work, but it'll be worth it.

51:57.407 --> 52:03.871
Because when he makes his vow to
the wrong girl, Odette will die.

52:03.872 --> 52:07.833
Then I'll finish Derek off myself.

52:07.834 --> 52:14.841
Oh, I love it. I mean,
this is really classy. This is me!

52:17.010 --> 52:19.512
♪ It's such a hoot to see them quaking ♪

52:20.597 --> 52:23.725
♪ When I'm king
They'll treat me with respect ♪

52:24.517 --> 52:28.187
♪ I can't wait to watch
Their poor hearts breaking ♪

52:28.188 --> 52:31.691
♪ So much for politically correct ♪

52:34.110 --> 52:38.363
♪ Up till now I've pulled my punches ♪

52:38.364 --> 52:41.408
♪ I intend to eat their lunches ♪

52:41.409 --> 52:45.580
♪ No more Mr. Nice Guy
Not for me ♪

52:48.917 --> 52:52.252
♪ If you think that I'm hard-hearted ♪

52:52.253 --> 52:56.298
♪ Well, lambie pie, I haven't even started ♪

52:56.299 --> 53:01.054
ALL: ♪ No more Mr. Nice Guy
No, sir-ee ♪

53:03.807 --> 53:06.851
♪ As soon as my witchcraft has zinged 'em ♪

53:07.602 --> 53:10.939
♪ I'll gain control of the kingdom ♪

53:11.439 --> 53:14.900
♪ As for Odette, well, that's tragic ♪

53:14.901 --> 53:19.364
♪ 'Cause I'm going back to that old black magic ♪

53:20.782 --> 53:24.368
♪ Good behavior, it's so much duller ♪

53:24.369 --> 53:28.205
♪ Time to show my one true color ♪

53:28.206 --> 53:33.627
♪ Baby, Mr. Nice Guy's history ♪

53:33.628 --> 53:34.712
[EXCLAIMS]

53:35.630 --> 53:39.132
♪ Vengeance is what I believe in ♪

53:39.133 --> 53:42.886
♪ I don't get mad, I get even ♪

53:42.887 --> 53:46.557
♪ Odette can't get to the ball
'Cause I won't bring her ♪

53:46.558 --> 53:50.645
♪ So I'll zap up a date who's a real dead ringer ♪

53:52.981 --> 53:56.567
♪ Up to no good, I love plotting ♪

53:56.568 --> 53:59.987
♪ 'Cause I'm so good when I'm rotten ♪

53:59.988 --> 54:05.576
♪ No more Mr. Nice Guy
Wait and see ♪

54:05.577 --> 54:11.164
- ♪ Wait and see ♪
- ♪ I'll become that nasty, naughty, dirty, spiteful ♪

54:11.165 --> 54:14.835
♪ Wicked, wayward, way delightful ♪

54:14.836 --> 54:19.090
♪ Bad guy I was born to be ♪

54:25.179 --> 54:27.015
One more time.

54:28.099 --> 54:31.852
♪ A lying, loathsome, never tender ♪

54:31.853 --> 54:35.439
♪ Indiscreet repeat offender ♪

54:35.440 --> 54:40.152
♪ No more Mr. Nice Guy
That's not me ♪

54:40.153 --> 54:42.070
ALL:
♪ Doo, doo, doo ♪♪

54:42.071 --> 54:43.406
ROTHBART:
Yeah!

54:47.702 --> 54:50.788
Thank you. Thank you. Thank you. Ha-ha.

54:52.957 --> 54:55.542
- Mother, have you se--?
- Oh, Derek.

54:55.543 --> 54:58.003
- What are these?
- Roses.

54:58.004 --> 55:00.297
- They're red.
- Of course they're red.

55:00.298 --> 55:03.091
But, Mom, I don't want red roses.

55:03.092 --> 55:05.636
I want white, like a swan.

55:05.637 --> 55:07.638
- Have you seen Bromley?
- No.

55:07.639 --> 55:09.973
DEREK:
Has anyone seen Bromley?

55:09.974 --> 55:11.892
Would you feed this to a swan?

55:11.893 --> 55:13.686
I...

55:14.228 --> 55:17.648
Take it back.
For something light, something fresh.

55:17.649 --> 55:18.650
[CRASHES]

55:19.108 --> 55:22.319
- No, no, no, Rogers, hold it.
- What's wrong?

55:22.320 --> 55:26.490
Tonight the music must be played <i>rubato.</i>

55:26.491 --> 55:29.743
Soft and graceful, like a swan.

55:29.744 --> 55:31.244
A swan?

55:31.245 --> 55:35.374
- You ever seen a swan, Rogers?
- Of course I've seen a swan.

55:35.375 --> 55:39.170
If you could play a swan,
what would it sound like?

55:40.463 --> 55:42.422
[HORN HONKS AND ROGERS CHUCKLES]

55:42.423 --> 55:45.301
Soft and graceful, Rogers.

55:46.302 --> 55:50.305
- Where is Bromley?
- No one has seen him, Derek.

55:50.306 --> 55:53.141
You're kidding. Who's gonna be my best man?

55:53.142 --> 55:55.186
Best...? You mean...?

55:56.521 --> 55:59.314
You... Oh, Derek.

55:59.315 --> 56:02.109
There you go, Rogers. That's the stuff.

56:02.110 --> 56:03.569
[BAND PLAYING SERENE MUSIC]

56:06.155 --> 56:07.489
Come on, Mother.

56:07.490 --> 56:09.492
[UBERTA CHUCKLING]

56:11.411 --> 56:14.497
Don't be so secretive, Derek.
Tell me who she is.

56:18.251 --> 56:19.210
[CHUCKLES]

56:22.505 --> 56:25.174
ROTHBART:
It hurts me to lock you up, Odette.

56:25.633 --> 56:27.844
Hurts me deep.

56:28.511 --> 56:33.140
But then, a king's day is
full of tough decisions.

56:33.141 --> 56:34.767
You understand.

56:35.893 --> 56:38.979
Oh... Now you're mad at me again.

56:38.980 --> 56:44.067
Doggone it, I can't do nothing right.
Head full of pudding.

56:44.068 --> 56:45.111
That's me.

56:46.946 --> 56:51.909
I can't leave you like this.
If you're not happy, I'm not happy.

56:53.036 --> 56:59.250
Hmm. I know. If you can't attend the ball,
then I'll bring the ball to you.

56:59.667 --> 57:00.792
Let's see.

57:00.793 --> 57:04.921
The first thing you'll need is a young man.

57:04.922 --> 57:09.927
The prince is busy, of course,
but I think I can arrange a substitute.

57:11.054 --> 57:14.098
No, please. I beg you. Please!

57:15.475 --> 57:18.227
Poor fella. He got lost in the woods.

57:20.646 --> 57:21.898
[SCREAMING]

57:25.443 --> 57:30.072
Help. Help! Don't go.

57:30.073 --> 57:36.829
Oh, I'd love to stay, but if I don't
leave now, I'll be late. That's tacky.

57:38.956 --> 57:43.127
Don't give me that look.
Had to be sneaky, didn't you?

57:43.586 --> 57:46.546
Had to drag your weakling prince into it.

57:46.547 --> 57:51.636
Well, that's fine with me.
Just fine with me!

57:56.015 --> 57:57.058
[PUFFIN GASPS]

57:59.977 --> 58:01.979
[♪♪♪]

58:19.247 --> 58:24.000
♪ Every single princess on the planet ♪

58:24.001 --> 58:28.755
♪ Prayed to be invited to the ball ♪

58:28.756 --> 58:33.426
ESCORTS:
♪ Every Portia, Guinevere and Janet ♪

58:33.427 --> 58:38.515
♪ Would come by coach or boat to be here
Most would swim the moat to be here ♪

58:38.516 --> 58:43.270
♪ Just to be at this historic gala ♪

58:43.271 --> 58:48.024
♪ Girls would walk or run or even crawl ♪

58:48.025 --> 58:52.654
♪ Rumor is that at this joyous scene tonight ♪

58:52.655 --> 58:58.619
♪ The prince will likely choose
His future queen tonight ♪♪

59:01.539 --> 59:05.626
Uh, excuse me. Oh, excuse me.

59:06.419 --> 59:11.381
- Ahem. Excuse me, Your Highness.
- Yes, yes, chamberlain?

59:11.382 --> 59:16.928
- It's getting rather crowded.
- Very well. You may begin the introductions.

59:16.929 --> 59:19.974
- And, chamberlain...
- Yes?

59:20.683 --> 59:25.020
No mistakes this time.
Everything must be perfect.

59:25.021 --> 59:28.732
Oh, no, no, no. Oh, yes.
I mean, oh, no, no, madam.

59:28.733 --> 59:30.776
Everything will be perfect.

59:32.403 --> 59:38.158
Promise me, Derek, you'll tell me who it is
the moment she arrives.

59:38.159 --> 59:44.165
Heh. Don't worry, Mother. You'll know.
Believe me, you'll know.

59:50.046 --> 59:51.129
Ah!

59:51.130 --> 59:52.589
- What?
- It's coming.

59:52.590 --> 59:56.927
- What is?
- An idea. A substantial idea.

59:56.928 --> 01:00:00.847
- A large, colossal idea!
- Sounds big.

01:00:00.848 --> 01:00:05.727
I got it! Water leaks
into the dungeon, right?

01:00:05.728 --> 01:00:09.440
Well, if there's a leak,
there must be a hole.

01:00:09.899 --> 01:00:12.484
We'll find the hole, make it bigger and...

01:00:12.485 --> 01:00:14.277
[IMITATES FLUSHING]

01:00:14.278 --> 01:00:16.196
She's loose. Heh-heh.

01:00:16.197 --> 01:00:19.158
I think you're forgetting two things.

01:00:21.285 --> 01:00:27.040
- His Majesty's got a point.
- Not to worry. Now, first we need a scout.

01:00:27.041 --> 01:00:31.127
Are you crazy?
Who's going to jump into this moat?

01:00:31.128 --> 01:00:34.130
- He's got to be a good swimmer.
- I should say so.

01:00:34.131 --> 01:00:36.132
He's gotta be small too.

01:00:36.133 --> 01:00:38.176
Teeny-weeny, not to be seen.

01:00:38.177 --> 01:00:41.513
And it wouldn't hurt if he was green,
for camouflage purposes.

01:00:41.514 --> 01:00:47.936
Precisely. Small, good swimmer, green--
Good grief. You're talking about me.

01:00:47.937 --> 01:00:51.231
♪ You're off on a mission
You're tough, in good condition ♪

01:00:51.232 --> 01:00:54.651
♪ A hero, warts and all
No fear! ♪♪

01:00:54.652 --> 01:00:55.986
[APPLAUSE]

01:00:55.987 --> 01:01:00.865
UBERTA: Oh, thank you.
I know some of you just abhor beauty pageants,

01:01:00.866 --> 01:01:07.956
but having been a puff-puff girl myself
way back in '39, I just couldn't resist.

01:01:07.957 --> 01:01:11.711
Girls. And a one, a two,
a one, two, three...

01:01:12.211 --> 01:01:14.213
[♪♪♪]

01:01:17.675 --> 01:01:22.178
♪ Beauty and glamour and breeding
Are matched ♪

01:01:22.179 --> 01:01:26.599
CHORUS:
♪ Princesses on parade ♪

01:01:26.600 --> 01:01:31.271
CHAMBERLAIN:
♪ Lovely, enthralling and all unattached ♪

01:01:31.272 --> 01:01:35.942
♪ The hoi polloi and those well-bred agree
Each enjoy a royal pedigree ♪

01:01:35.943 --> 01:01:37.444
CHORUS:
♪ Born for success ♪

01:01:37.445 --> 01:01:40.238
♪ Each possesses a spark ♪

01:01:40.239 --> 01:01:44.743
♪ Each a remarkable maid ♪

01:01:44.744 --> 01:01:49.414
♪ Boy, oh, boy, these royal highnesses
All have plusses, they've no minuses ♪

01:01:49.415 --> 01:01:56.422
- ♪ Gaze upon ♪
CHORUS: ♪ These princesses on parade ♪

01:01:58.090 --> 01:02:02.761
♪ This princess comes from Colchester
Where corn and cotton grows ♪

01:02:02.762 --> 01:02:07.307
♪ She plays croquet and harpsichord
And sews her own clothes ♪

01:02:07.308 --> 01:02:11.728
♪ Antonia isn't known to take
The path of least resistance ♪

01:02:11.729 --> 01:02:16.316
♪ She hails from Southeast Harristan
And came the farthest distance ♪

01:02:16.317 --> 01:02:20.945
♪ Griselda lives to help the world
She finds no task too menial ♪

01:02:20.946 --> 01:02:25.533
♪ And all the other hopeful girls think
She's the most congenial ♪

01:02:25.534 --> 01:02:29.829
♪ Brunhilde is from Stuttgart
Where our swords and armor's made ♪

01:02:29.830 --> 01:02:32.582
Gaze upon...

01:02:32.583 --> 01:02:39.005
CHORUS:
♪ Princesses on parade ♪

01:02:39.006 --> 01:02:43.176
♪ This is the likely occasion ♪

01:02:43.177 --> 01:02:47.681
♪ When the heir to the throne picks a wife ♪

01:02:48.182 --> 01:02:52.894
PRINCESSES: ♪ This may be the day
That Prince Derek will say ♪

01:02:52.895 --> 01:02:57.941
♪ "Where have you been all my life?" ♪

01:02:57.942 --> 01:02:59.944
[ALL SIGHING]

01:03:01.529 --> 01:03:05.865
ALL: ♪ Brilliant, beguiling
A smiling brigade ♪

01:03:05.866 --> 01:03:10.121
CHAMBERLAIN:
♪ Princesses on parade ♪

01:03:10.704 --> 01:03:16.668
CHORUS: ♪ Each the pride of her community
Each a golden opportunity ♪

01:03:16.669 --> 01:03:19.879
PRINCESSES:
♪ Just the thought that Crown Prince Derek ♪

01:03:19.880 --> 01:03:22.882
♪ Will face this choice and he's hysterical ♪

01:03:22.883 --> 01:03:26.719
CHORUS:
♪ Gaze upon, heap praise upon ♪

01:03:26.720 --> 01:03:29.639
♪ These radiant, glamorous, luminous, dazzling ♪

01:03:29.640 --> 01:03:36.480
ALL:
♪ Princesses on parade ♪♪

01:03:41.277 --> 01:03:43.279
[APPLAUSE]

01:03:45.322 --> 01:03:46.740
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

01:03:47.491 --> 01:03:49.201
- Ah!
- Chamberlain.

01:03:50.661 --> 01:03:55.957
All who were invited are
present, are they not?

01:03:55.958 --> 01:03:57.625
Well, yes. I mean...

01:03:57.626 --> 01:03:59.544
[KNOCKING CONTINUES]

01:03:59.545 --> 01:04:05.842
- Open the door, heh-heh, chamberlain.
- Who could it possibly be? I checked my list.

01:04:05.843 --> 01:04:09.096
It's the milkman. It must be the milkman.

01:04:10.055 --> 01:04:10.931
[GASPS]

01:04:18.689 --> 01:04:20.523
Well, it's not the milkman.

01:04:20.524 --> 01:04:22.526
[♪♪♪]

01:04:27.406 --> 01:04:28.407
UBERTA:
Oh...

01:04:29.116 --> 01:04:31.368
Oh, no, it can't be.

01:04:37.791 --> 01:04:40.878
Excuse me. Pardon me, please.
I've got to get through.

01:04:41.212 --> 01:04:44.882
Oh, yes. She's lovely, isn't she?

01:04:45.508 --> 01:04:47.718
Queen coming through here.
Excuse me, excuse me.

01:04:49.803 --> 01:04:55.308
- Rogers! Rogers! Who is it? Do you know her?
- I don't know.

01:04:55.309 --> 01:04:59.729
Come now, Rogers.
I know he confides in you. Who is it?!

01:04:59.730 --> 01:05:02.316
I promise, I've never seen her before.

01:05:03.275 --> 01:05:07.947
Although,
she does look a great deal like...

01:05:08.822 --> 01:05:10.324
But it couldn't be.

01:05:12.409 --> 01:05:13.452
Could it?

01:05:16.539 --> 01:05:21.460
- Oh, I was so worried. I almost thought--
- Nothing could keep me away.

01:05:23.337 --> 01:05:25.339
[BAND PLAYING SWEEPING MUSIC]

